Package arrayGenerator.scope

Defines scopes and provides some implementations thereof.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Scope<T>
    A scope represents a set of values - for example, an alphabet of characters, or a range of integers.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AlphabetScope<T>
    Implements Scope, when the set (or alphabet) of possible values is specified by a Set.
    CharacterScope
    An implementation of an AlphabetScope for characters.
    IntegerScope
    Implements a scope of integers.
    StringScope
    An implementation of an AlphabetScope for string.

Package arrayGenerator.scope Description

Defines scopes and provides some implementations thereof. A scope defines a set of values. A scope can be used to provide a set of acceptable values for an ArrayGenerator.
